---
layout: layouts/_base.njk
title: "Community Week NYC × RadicalxChange"
description: "A live conversation with NYC community builders during Community Week NYC (May 9–17, 2026)."
permalink: /communityweeknyc/index.html
introBlurb: |
  This is a partnership to gather structured, cross-cutting insight from the
  600 community builders convening for [Community Week NYC](https://www.communityweek.nyc/). Together we are
  asking, in public and in real time, what community builders need to do their
  work — and what would have to change for that work to be properly
  resourced.

  The conversation is built around two questions:

  1. **What skills, resources, and infrastructure** do community builders need
     to sustain and grow their work?
  2. **What would a *community economy*** — grants, residencies, civic
     infrastructure — look like in practice?

  The bigger picture: community is civic infrastructure, and it is currently
  under-resourced, under-recognised, and under-invested in. This conversation
  is a first step toward building the evidence base for change.
cwnycBlurb: |
  [Community Week NYC](https://www.communityweek.nyc) is a citywide celebration of belonging that spotlights
  the organizers, spaces, and communities connecting New Yorkers. From May
  9–17, 2026, communities across all five boroughs will host events built on
  a shared belief: that being intentional about belonging builds deeper
  relationships, healthier cities, and stronger local economies. Presented by
  [Sugary NYC]9https://www.sugarynyc.com/about) and [week nights](https://weeknights.co/).
rxcBlurb: |
  [RadicalxChange Foundation](/) is a 501(c)(3) nonprofit organization
  dedicated to democratic innovation and institutional design through
  operational partnerships and experimental projects between academia,
  government, art, technology, and beyond.
closingBlurb: |
  Join us at **"The Future of Social Connection"** on **May 15 2026**, where Jack Henderson will present a
  report-back from the engagement.
---

<!-- prettier-ignore -->
{% import "components/menu.njk" as menu %}
<!-- prettier-ignore -->
{% import "components/footer.njk" as footer %}
<!-- prettier-ignore -->
{% import "components/logo.njk" as logo %}

<!-- prettier-ignore -->
{% block otherHead %}
<style>
  .cwnyc-polis-embed {
    min-height: 600px;
  }
  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .cwnyc-polis-embed {
      min-height: 700px;
    }
  }
  /* pol.is/embed.js sets max-width: 0 on the injected iframe; reset it so the
     iframe fills the wrapper. Also ensure it has visible height. */
  .cwnyc-polis-embed iframe {
    width: 100% !important;
    max-width: 100% !important;
    min-height: 600px;
    border: 0;
    display: block;
  }
</style>
<!-- prettier-ignore -->
{% endblock %}

<!-- prettier-ignore -->
{{ menu.render() }}

<div
  class="relative grid grid-cols-layout-4 lg:grid-cols-layout-12 py-margin lg:py-lg/margin bg-golden-fizz"
>
  <!-- Co-branded logos -->
  <header
    class="col-span-columns flex flex-wrap items-center gap-x-6 gap-y-4 mb-12 lg:mb-16"
  >
    <a href="/" class="block" aria-label="RadicalxChange home">
      <img
        src="/images/logos/logo.svg"
        width="566"
        height="97"
        alt="RadicalxChange"
        class="h-12 lg:h-16 w-auto"
      />
    </a>
    <span aria-hidden="true" class="font-display text-size-2 lg:text-size-4 leading-none"
      >×</span
    >
    <a
      href="https://www.communityweek.nyc"
      target="_blank"
      rel="noopener noreferrer"
      class="block"
      aria-label="Community Week NYC"
    >
      <!--
        TODO(cwnyc-logo): a transparent-background SVG (or PNG) is preferred
        and pending from CWNYC. The current asset is the official 1024×537
        wordmark + pigeon banner on a solid blue background — displaying
        as-is per partner direction until the transparent version arrives.
      -->
      <img
        src="/images/communityweeknyc/cwnyc-logo.png"
        width="1024"
        height="537"
        alt="Community Week NYC, May 9–17 2026"
        class="h-16 lg:h-24 w-auto"
      />
    </a>
  </header>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <div class="col-span-columns lg:col-start-column-1 lg:col-end-gutter-9 mb-12 lg:mb-16">
    <h1 class="font-display text-size-display lg:text-size-lg/display uppercase">
      What do community builders need to thrive?
    </h1>
    <p class="mt-line-3/2 text-size-1 lg:text-size-2">
      A live conversation with NYC community builders during Community Week NYC.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- Intro -->
  <section
    class="col-span-columns lg:col-start-column-1 lg:col-end-gutter-9 mb-16"
  >
    <div class="markdown">
      {{ introBlurb | markdown | safe }}
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Polis embed -->
  <section
    id="join"
    class="col-span-columns mb-16 scroll-mt-8"
  >
    <h2
      class="font-display text-size-2 lg:text-size-4 uppercase mb-4"
    >
      Join the conversation
    </h2>
    <p class="mb-6 text-size-0 lg:text-size-1">
      Vote on statements from other community builders, and add your own. It
      takes 2 minutes.
    </p>

    <!--
      Polis embed — Polis's documented script-based pattern
      (https://compdemocracy.org/Polis/). The script auto-creates an iframe
      pointing at https://pol.is/<conversation_id>/embed.

      The conversation_id appears in two places on this page; keep them in sync:
        1. data-conversation_id on the .polis div below
        2. the href on the "Open the conversation in a new tab" fallback link

      The inline guard below preserves a "coming soon" fallback if the ID is
      ever reverted to the POLIS_CONVO_ID_TODO sentinel — useful if the
      conversation needs to be taken offline temporarily.

      Fallback link: a direct "Open in a new tab" link is rendered beneath the
      embed in case the iframe fails to load (CSP, ad-blockers, etc.).
    -->
    <div
      class="cwnyc-polis-embed border-2 border-black bg-white relative overflow-hidden"
    >
      <div class="polis" data-conversation_id="6epckxncim"></div>
      <div
        class="cwnyc-polis-placeholder absolute inset-0 hidden flex-col items-center justify-center text-center p-8"
      >
        <p class="font-bold uppercase text-size-0 mb-2">
          Polis embed — coming soon
        </p>
        <p class="text-size--1 text-gray max-w-md">
          The live conversation will appear here once it is seeded.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <script>
      (function () {
        var slot = document.querySelector(".cwnyc-polis-embed .polis");
        if (!slot) return;
        var id = slot.getAttribute("data-conversation_id");
        if (!id || id === "POLIS_CONVO_ID_TODO") {
          slot.style.display = "none";
          var ph = document.querySelector(".cwnyc-polis-placeholder");
          if (ph) {
            ph.classList.remove("hidden");
            ph.classList.add("flex");
          }
          return;
        }
        var s = document.createElement("script");
        s.async = true;
        s.src = "https://pol.is/embed.js";
        document.head.appendChild(s);
      })();
    </script>

    <p class="mt-4 text-size--1">
      Trouble loading?
      <a
        href="https://pol.is/6epckxncim"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        class="inline-link"
      >
        Open the conversation in a new tab →
      </a>
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- About the partners -->
  <section
    class="col-span-columns lg:col-start-column-1 lg:col-end-margin-2 mb-16"
  >
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-x-12 gap-y-8">
      <div>
        <h3 class="font-bold uppercase mb-4 text-size-0">
          About Community Week NYC
        </h3>
        <div class="markdown markdown-sm">
          {{ cwnycBlurb | markdown | safe }}
        </div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="font-bold uppercase mb-4 text-size-0">
          About RadicalxChange
        </h3>
        <div class="markdown markdown-sm">
          {{ rxcBlurb | markdown | safe }}
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Closing -->
  <section
    class="col-span-columns lg:col-start-column-1 lg:col-end-gutter-9 space-y-line-3/2"
  >
    <div class="markdown markdown-sm">
      {{ closingBlurb | markdown | safe }}
    </div>
    <p class="text-size--1">
      Contact:
      <a href="mailto:info@radicalxchange.org" class="inline-link"
        >info@radicalxchange.org</a
      >
      (RadicalxChange) and
      <a href="mailto:hello@communityweek.nyc" class="inline-link"
        >hello@communityweek.nyc</a
      >
      (Community Week NYC).
    </p>
    <p class="text-size--1">
      <strong>Community Week participant?</strong> RxC is offering a free online
      workshop later —
      <a href="mailto:info@radicalxchange.org" class="inline-link"
        >get in touch</a
      >.
    </p>
  </section>
</div>

<!-- prettier-ignore -->
{{ footer.render() }}

